http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Curbs-on-train-services/article13987861.ece

Long-distance trains plying through the State will be regulated from Friday in view of the dismantling of the road overbridge between Byculla and the Chatrapati Shivaji Terminus (CST) station in Mumbai under the Central Railway.Train 16340 Nagercoil-Mumbai CST Express scheduled to leave Nagercoil at 6.30 a.m. on January 8 and train 16339 Mumbai CST-Nagercoil Express scheduled to leave Mumbai CST at 12.10 p.m. on January 10 have been cancelled, according to the Railways.Partial cancellationTrain 16382 Kanyakumari-Mumbai CST (Jayanthi Janatha Express) leaving Kanyakumari on January 8 will be terminate in Pune. Subsequently, train 16381 Mumbai CST-Kanyakumari (Jayanthi Janatha Express) scheduled to leave Mumbai CST at 3.45 p.m. on January 10 will start from Pune at 7.35 p.m.Train 16332 Thiruvananthapuram-Mumbai CST Weekly Express departing from Thiruvanathapuram Central on January 9 is likely to get delayed in the Mumbai area by over two-and-a-half hours.